* 2 IP : Master and Node
* Disable Swap
* Share keys. Create new Authorized key file and copy past id rsa pub
* check whether ssh bridgeadapterip  [Root login aaganum, Not user login. Athuvum password illama straight ah ulla poganum]

1. Install RKE

>> Download RKE Binary

https://github.com/rancher/rke/releases/

>> Using winscp dowload to server
>> Rename to rke and copy to /usr/local/bin
>> Change permission 777
>> Testing :  # rke --version
Output : rke version v1.0.6


2. Install Docker

https://ranchermanager.docs.rancher.com/v2.5/getting-started/installation-and-upgrade/installation-requirements/install-docker

# curl https://releases.rancher.com/install-docker/20.10.sh | sh


3. Creating Cluster Configuration file

# rke config

By doing this we will get cluster.yaml file

>> Follow as per screen

Later will run this cluster.yaml file



4. Deploying Kubernetes

# rke up


